gomodel:SYNGO_5582  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Talin-2 interacts with PIPK (phosphatidylinositol-(4)-phosphate 5-kinase type Iγ).\n\nFigure 3: Microinjection of PIPK pep disrupts the actin cytoskeleton at synapses.\n\nFigure 5: over-expression of human talin 2 head (aa 1-438, GST fusion protein) at lamprey synapses causes ultrastructural changes. (analogous data in Figure 4 for PIPK)\n\nAuthors conclude:\n\"the interaction of PIP kinase with talin in presynaptic compartments provides a mechanism to coordinate PI(4,5)P2 synthesis, actin dynamics, and endocytosis, and further supports a functional link between actin and clathrin-mediated endocytosis.\". Experimental description: evidence is shown for both Human and Lamprey Talin-2, we annotated the former;\n\"Human PIPKIγ tail (aa 635-662) and human talin 2 head (aa 1-438) were expressed as GST fusion proteins and purified using a standard protocol\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5582" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

